										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Thanks the promotional interests, I&#8217;ve been unable to keep this blog on it&#8217;s proper schedule.  But now that Trick is out and Waking 2nd Ed is all finish, we can get back to the eye-candy and silly steamy things!  Huzzah!  So, without further adieu, here&#8217;s some pretty to brighten your Sunday.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.jue.so/home/Works/1190/1/173" target="_blank"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="aligncenter" alt="" src="http://www.jue.so/UpLoad/WorksPhoto/173/ce7e826f2b74cd19.jpg" width="606" height="404" /></a>Click images for more of each.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.jue.so/home/Works/1190/1/173" target="_blank"><img decoding="async" alt="" src="http://www.jue.so/UpLoad/WorksPhoto/173/e034a62a1828bfae.jpg" width="275" height="184" /></a>  <a href="http://www.jue.so/home/Works/1190/1/173" target="_blank"><img decoding="async" alt="" src="http://www.jue.so/UpLoad/WorksPhoto/173/19860f1ec5f5fa14.jpg" width="275" height="184" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.jue.so/home/Works/1190/1/585" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter" alt="" src="http://www.jue.so/UpLoad/WorksPhoto/585/bd41dd4a8802a431.jpg" width="672" height="962" /></a></p>
<p><a style="line-height:1.5em;" href="http://www.jue.so/home/Works/1190/1/585" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" alt="" src="http://www.jue.so/UpLoad/WorksPhoto/585/1faa29beb810b580.jpg" width="275" height="184" /></a>  <a href="http://www.jue.so/home/Works/1190/1/585" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" alt="" src="http://www.jue.so/UpLoad/WorksPhoto/585/f0fcd784e4afa35a.jpg" width="275" height="184" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align:left;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter" alt="" src="http://www.jue.so/UpLoad/WorksPhoto/585/388e5ce266d2f52d.jpg" width="672" height="979" /><a href="http://www.jue.so/home/Works/1190/1/1852" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter" alt="" src="http://www.jue.so/UpLoad/WorksPhoto/1852/c078359df5269392.jpg" width="672" height="448" /></a> <a href="http://www.jue.so/home/Works/1190/1/1852" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter" alt="" src="http://www.jue.so/UpLoad/WorksPhoto/1852/d35e046e6e7f7d0e.jpg" width="672" height="448" /></a><a href="http://www.jue.so/home/Works/1190/1/1852" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter" alt="" src="http://www.jue.so/UpLoad/WorksPhoto/1852/b00d6b9d82eb6189.jpg" width="672" height="1007" /></a>Aren&#8217;t these pieces just lovely?  Be sure to check out the rest of this amazing art over at <a href="http://www.jue.so/home/Works/1190/" target="_blank">Hu Shaoming&#8217;s site</a>.</p>
<p style="text-align:left;">&#8212;</p>
<p style="text-align:left;">Are you an artist/photographer/sculptor who loves Steampunk as much as I do?   Would you like to see your work featured on this blog?  Or, do you know of someone else who’s work you adore?  Please leave a comment on this post with a link or two!   I’ll happily feature anything that I think will fit the style of my blog.  And even if I don’t feature it, please please leave your info in a comment anyway!  More art is always better than less.</p>
